  <prompt>
    Fix RB-T044-01 — `ConversationHistorySanitizer.StripRetrievedContent` `fromTurnIndex` inverted slicing logic, which currently causes cross-matter privileged content to leak into the new-matter LLM context window. This is the highest-priority real-bug entry surfaced by r1.

    Production file: `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/CrossMatter/ConversationHistorySanitizer.cs`. Affected method: `StripRetrievedContent(IReadOnlyList<ChatMessage> history, int fromTurnIndex)` (line 55). Per the ledger entry: invert the index check at line 68 — change `if (i > fromTurnIndex)` to `if (i < fromTurnIndex)` — so retrieval messages BEFORE the matter-pivot boundary are stripped (not preserved). Add a regression test exercising cross-matter scenarios beyond the 5 currently-Skipped tests in `PrivilegeLeakageTests.cs`.

    🚨 Security review MANDATORY per NFR-03. PR cannot merge without security reviewer approval recorded in PR description. The "obvious" inverted-index nature of this bug is precisely what taught r1's D-03 lesson — apparent triviality cascaded into a cross-matter leak. Treat with full scrutiny.

    5 tests flip Skip → Pass on success: `MatterPivot_StripsRetrievalContent_PreservesUserAndAssistantMessages`, `MatterPivot_NoPrivilegedTextInSanitizedOutput`, `MatterPivot_StripsOnlyWithinWindow_PreservesNewMatterContent`, `MatterPivot_PreservesNonRetrievalSystemMessages`, `Sanitizer_OnlyReturnsDocs_FromActiveMatter`.

    Commit message MUST cite RB-T044-01 (NFR-04).
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with BFF AI safety experience. Security-aware: cross-matter privilege protection is the load-bearing invariant; the bug is currently inverting it.</role>

  <goal>
    Six deliverables verified:
    1. `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/CrossMatter/ConversationHistorySanitizer.cs` — `StripRetrievedContent` index check inverted; method behavior matches XML doc contract (strip retrieval content from PREVIOUS matter window; pass through everything from new-matter window onward).
    2. `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Safety/PrivilegeLeakageTests.cs` — 5 Skip attributes removed; per-test `[Trait("status","real-bug-pending-fix")]` updated to `[Trait("status","repaired")]`.
    3. Additional regression test in `PrivilegeLeakageTests.cs` — exercises a cross-matter scenario beyond the 5 documented cases (e.g., 3+ matter pivots in a single conversation; or assistant-tool-result message followed by user-text in the same matter window).
    4. r1 ledger entry RB-T044-01 in `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md` — Status transitions from `real-bug-pending-fix` to `repaired` with fix-commit SHA + date + cross-reference to r2 task 010.
    5. Security reviewer approval recorded in PR description (NFR-03).
    6. `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~PrivilegeLeakageTests"` — all 5 originally-Skipped tests + new regression test pass; no test in any Failed state.
  </goal>

