  <context>
    <background>
      r1 task 044 (P23.H5 — Ai/Safety) filed RB-T044-01 on 2026-05-31. The documented contract (XML doc line 41 of `ConversationHistorySanitizer.cs`): when the user switches from Matter A to Matter B, any tool_result messages from Matter A are replaced with a privacy placeholder. The implementation does the OPPOSITE: messages where `i > fromTurnIndex` (new matter side) are passed through verbatim, and only `i <= fromTurnIndex` (old matter side) are considered — but since `fromTurnIndex` points to the start of the previous matter window (where the matter marker is, not a retrieval message), nothing in that range gets stripped. Result: retrieval content from the OLD matter leaks into the NEW matter LLM context.

      r1's D-03 lesson: "obvious" fixes still cascade. The inverted-index nature of the bug LOOKS like a one-line fix, but production runtime impact is cross-matter privilege leakage. Security review is non-negotiable. Step 9.5 quality gates run code-review + adr-check; an additional security review pass is required per NFR-03 before PR merge. Identity of named security reviewer is captured in Phase 0 outreach (task 002) — task 010 cannot complete without that name in place.

      Cluster fix considerations: RB-T044-02..05 share `CitationExtractor.cs` as production target — those are Phase 2 entries (MEDIUM severity). Do NOT bundle here. This task closes RB-T044-01 only.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
