  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read RB-T044-01 entry in `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md` end-to-end; load `ConversationHistorySanitizer.cs` + `PrivilegeLeakageTests.cs` + interface + supporting models.</step>
    <step order="2">Confirm with the named security reviewer (from task 002) that they are available for this PR's review window; abort task with documented hold if no reviewer is named.</step>
    <step order="3">Verify the bug by removing the Skip attribute on ONE of the 5 cited tests locally; run; observe failure; restore Skip. (Task 001 already did this in aggregate; this is the per-task confirmation step.)</step>
    <step order="4">Apply the production fix at `ConversationHistorySanitizer.cs` line ~68: invert the index check per ledger recommendation. Verify the XML doc contract still describes the (now-fixed) behavior; clarify the doc if needed (same-line edit; not a contract change).</step>
    <step order="5">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — confirm 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="6">Update the 5 cited tests in `PrivilegeLeakageTests.cs`: remove `Skip = "..."` attributes; change per-test `[Trait("status","real-bug-pending-fix")]` to `[Trait("status","repaired")]`. Run `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~PrivilegeLeakageTests"`; confirm all 5 pass.</step>
    <step order="7">Add ONE new regression test in `PrivilegeLeakageTests.cs` exercising a cross-matter scenario beyond the 5 documented (e.g., 3+ matter pivots; or assistant-tool-result followed by user-text in same window). Confirm it passes. This satisfies bff-extensions.md § F test-update obligation.</step>
    <step order="8">Run focused test suite: `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Services.Ai.Safety"` — confirm 0 failures + no regressions across the full Safety surface.</step>
    <step order="9">Run Step 9.5 quality gates: `code-review` + `adr-check` skills (per FULL rigor). Address any findings before proceeding.</step>
    <step order="10">PR creation: cite RB-T044-01 + resolution mode (`repaired`) in commit message + PR title; in PR description, add a dedicated "Security review" section with the named reviewer + checklist (privilege-leak scenarios covered; XML doc contract verified; new regression test exercises additional cross-matter paths). Wait for named reviewer's approval before merge.</step>
    <step order="11">After PR merge: update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md` — transition RB-T044-01 Status from `real-bug-pending-fix` (or `assigned-to-r2`/`in-progress`) to `repaired` with fix-commit SHA + date + cross-reference to r2 task 010.</step>
    <step order="12">Update `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` — mark 010 as ✅; update `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

